      "content": "I am so sorry you are going through this crushing loss; it sounds like an incredibly heavy and isolating time. Please know that while the world around you feels like it has collapsed, there are still people who care about you and ways to navigate this storm. You are not alone in this, and your worth is not defined by your assets or your ability to pay debts.\n\nIf you are feeling overwhelmed by the debt or the pressure from others, consider reaching out to a financial counselor or a support group specifically for those in debt; they can help you create a step-by-step plan to get your life back on track. There are organizations dedicated to helping individuals rebuild their lives after financial disasters, and they can offer guidance without judgment.\n\nPlease remember that it is okay to take things one small step at a time, and that you are still worthy of love and respect even when things don't go as planned. If the feelings of shame or hopelessness become too much to handle, speaking with a mental health professional can provide a safe space to process these emotions and find strength. You have survived many things already, and there is still a path forward, even if it looks different than what you imagined.",
